SIMPLE: undo
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Undo
<hw>Un*do"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>und<?/n</ets>. See 1st <er>Un-</er>, and Do to perform.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>To reverse, as what has been done; to annul; to bring
to naught.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>What's done can not be <qex>undone</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To-morrow, ere the setting sun,⟦br⟧
She 'd all <qex>undo</qex> that she had done.</q>
<rj><qau>Swift.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To loose; to open; to take to piece; to unfasten; to
untie; hence, to unravel; to solve; <as>as, to <ex>undo</ex> a knot; to
<ex>undo</ex> a puzzling question; to <ex>undo</ex> a riddle</as>.</def>
<rj><au>Tennyson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Pray you, <qex>undo</qex> this button.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>She took the spindle, and <qex>undoing</qex> the thread gradually,
measured it.</q> <rj><qau>Sir W. Scott.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To bring to poverty; to impoverish; to ruin, as in
reputation, morals, hopes, or the like; <as>as, many are <ex>undone</ex>
by unavoidable losses, but more <ex>undo</ex> themselves by vices and
dissipation, or by indolence</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>That quaffing and drinking will <qex>undo</qex> you,</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Undock</ent>⟦br⟧
